    1.16.200 (#1708)
    
    * Initial 1.16.100 support
    
    CreativeContentPacket is corrupting for some odd reason and crashing the client.
    
    * Many performance changes & fix crashing
    
    * Remove remapping and send pre-mapped values
    
    * Fixes for skins, commands and inventories (#1685)
    
    - Fixed client crashing on Windows 10 (when you use persona-skin).
    - Added new parameter for SkinAnimation - "AnimationExpression".
    - Fixed commands enabling.
    - Fixed opening / closing inventories on client-side.
    
    Co-authored-by: xBeeegsone <xbeeegsone@users.noreply.github.com>
    
    * fix for skin + geometry, for entityhumans (#1688)
    
    * Item translations using item palette (#1694)
    
    * Move batching code down to RakNetInterface
    
    * Fix ContainerClosePacket (#1696)
    
    * Update Sound enum to 1.16.100 (#1693)

    * initial 1.16.200 support (#1707)
    
    * fix for skin + geometry, for entityhumans
    
    * initial 1.16.200 support
    
    * change comment
    
    * Don't batch batched packets
    
    * Remove extra data from chunk encoding
    
    * Refactor packet batching code
    
    * More refactoring of RakNetInterface
    
    - Should improve performance further as we are now decompressing packets on the network threads unlike before.
    - May fix the disconnect issues but I haven't been able to reproduce it so can't be certain it does.
    - PlayerCreationEvent was being called async which could have caused further issues. It is now queued onto the main thread.
    - Broken packets from the client will now cause them to be force disconnected from the server.
    - Bumped RakNet to 1.6.25
    
    * Don't batch broadcasted packets
    
    * Catch and log errors whilst handling packets
    
    * Don't encode packets on netty threads
    
    * Remove RakNet testing version

commit 090684492c36dc8562c49c795d52997dbdcfd529
Author: PetteriM1 <petteri.malkavaara1@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun May 17 21:13:42 2020 +0300

    Don't run checkInteractNearby on every tick (#1443)
    
    Whatever this method is required for (something with vehicle interaction on mobile I guess) it surely doesn't have to run on every tick. Because of the usage of `getEntityPlayerLookingAt` not running this on every tick will improve the server performance especially when there are many players online. I didn't find any side effects from this change.

4	1	src/main/java/cn/nukkit/Player.java

    * Fixes Crafting
    
    interactPacket.ACTION_MOUSEOVER is sent multiple times which instantly
    cancels any craftingType as craftingType is set to  CRAFTING_SMALL every
    time the Interact_Packet is sent to the server. If a player walks past
    the crafting player is possibly will cause the bug to happen again.
    Maybe a long term fix is to only set the craftingType in a valid action
    like ACTION_LEFT_CLICK/ACTION_RIGHT_CLICK/ACTION_VEHICLE_EXIT ?
    
    * Maybe this is better than https://github.com/yescallop/Nukkit/pull/12
    
    * Add InventoryClickEvent, called when classic GUI (win10) player click and hold a item from an inventory window.
    Now you can do something interesting like PC servers.

    Farmland is hydrated how it is described in Minecraft Wiki (http://minecraft.gamepedia.com/Farmland): (#1734)
    
    "A farmland block will be created dry. It will become hydrated if the following conditions are met:
    1) Water up to four blocks away horizontally, including diagonals.
    2) The water must be on the same level or 1 block above farmland block level."
    
    Allow scheduled  update for BlockWaterStill.

commit 1e5242a38ac7e7a4ac2f9d0b6a075a4b87639a56
Author: Tee7even <Tee7even@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon May 1 23:00:48 2017 +0400

    Oops, I broke your plugins! (#1707)
    
    You may want to update your plugins before using this. The changes are:
    - Integer side constants in Vector3 are replaced with the BlockFace enum.
    - Reworked EntityDamageEvent:
      - Integer constants are replaced with enums: DamageCause and DamageModifier.
      - attack method of Entity class now returns a boolean value: true if damage was dealt to an entity and false if not.
      - The event is not fired if server determines that no damage was dealt to an entity (for example if player is in creative mode or the last damage was not enough time ago), so the vanilla behaviour now can't be broken by de-cancelling it.
    - Redstone by @Creeperface01. There's done pretty much, but not everything works just yet.

commit 5d219d8ab8758efee8656acff6a048646f3ff46a
Author: daveboden <dave@daveboden.com>
Date:   Mon Dec 5 12:00:05 2016 +0000

    Check y coordinate as part of .equals() so that even thought the hashcode of valid bedrock point (80, 0, 100) and invalid (80, 255, 100) will have the same hashcode due to y being << shifted 24 bits, the .equals() method will show that they're different.
    Change is relevant for scripts that expect 0 (Air) to be returned for invalid coordinates.

commit 15e1b88e6e389ddf7453fa6ae6e90adc413c9b35
Author: Jesse Boyd <jessepaleg@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Oct 4 08:33:29 2016 +1100

    Some improvements
    
    Use Long/BlockVector3 instead of strings for maps
    Reduce cache size significantly by not storing redundant data
    Reduce login time significantly by reducing min chunk radius
    Reduce chunk load by avoiding processing extra data
    Reduce memory usage by storing cache in weak map
    Reduce memory usage by unloading chunks more often
    Reduce memory usage by using soft reference for some block updates
    - If gc'd it will send a chunk update instead (less memory usage)
    Optimize collision checks
    Optimize various things by reusing objects and avoiding unnecesary
    creation
    Add debug level 0 = does not log to file

commit a68ec62ecf4db20317fea9b5b1d6e547d323f49b
Author: fromgate <fromgate@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Feb 11 10:34:44 2016 +0300

    Added SimpleConfig class
    
    SimpleConfig is a class that created to made working with config files easier.
    It based on built-in Nukkit Config class (using this class to save/load operations).
    
    ```
    public class TestCfg extends SimpleConfig {
        public TestCfg(PluginBase plugin) {
            super(plugin);
        }
    
        @Path (value = "test.string")
        public String testString = "test string";
    
        @Path (value = "test.integer")
        public int testInt = 10;
    
        @Path (value = "test.list")
        public List<String> testStringList = new ArrayList<String>(Arrays.asList("test 1", "test 2", "test 3"));
    }
    ```
    
    To use config now must create a TestCfg object:
    
    ```
    TestCfg cfg = new TestCfg(this);
    cfg.load(); // loading data from config.yml
    cfg.save(); // saving data to config.yml
    ```
    
    After executing cfg.save() you'll find a config.yml in your plugin folder:
    ```
    test:
       string: "test string"
       integer: 10
       list:
       - test 1
       - test 2
       - test 3
    
    ```
    
    To access to config values, you just need to use TestCfg fields as usually. After modification of the fields, you must call save() method to save data to file.
    ```
    cfg.testInt = 100;
    cfg.save();
    player.sendMessage("Test string from config: "+cfg.testString);
    ```

108	0	src/main/java/cn/nukkit/utils/SimpleConfig.java
